				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">How fast is your "modern, low-power processor"? If it's fast enough, perhaps one of the existing NES emulators could be ported. If it's an ARM, and you can make a simple tile display engine (read: a PPU less accurate than Nesticle's yet good enough), you can probably repurpose the PocketNES emulator to emulate the CPU and APU. PocketNES itself needs only about 16.8 MHz of an ARM7TDMI CPU, but it high-level-emulates the PPU by telling the Game Boy Advance PPU to display the same tiles.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

