				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The UZEBox is pretty freakin awesome <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> I got as far as making a Pong machine out of an ATTiny2313 and a simple R2R ladder, but this thing blows me away.
<br />
<br />UZEBox is based on an ATMega644. That has 64KB of PRG ROM (32K instructions + data storage, minus UZEBox libraries and boot loader) and 4KB of RAM (minus the VRAM, don't know how much this is). I'd be willing to bet you could squeeze SMB1 on there if you coded it by hand. A machine translation might be ROM-constrained due to the 16-bit instruction word size.</div>

